Key Match Events: Pakistan scored 185 runs after losing 9 wickets.
South Africa made a slow start and then lost momentum post-rains.
Pakistan's Shadab Khan and Iftikhar Ahmed scored 52 and 51 runs respectively.
Anrich Nortje was the key bowler for South Africa, taking 4 wickets.
South Africa lost 9 wickets in 20 overs.
Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan won the toss and decided to bat first.
Harsha Bhogle called Shadab Khan a 'proper all rounder'.
Former cricketer Alen Wilkins praised Pakistan's T20 performance.
Robin Uthappa praised team Pakistan for its victory against South Africa.
Mohammad Hafeez congratulated team Pakistan and applauded Shadab Khan and Iftikhar Ahmed.
Pakistan kept alive its T20 World Cup dream with Shadab Khan and Iftikhar Ahmed's performance.
Post-Match Reflections: Babar Azam expressed joy over the victory and credited Haris for maintaining momentum.
Shadab Khan was announced the Player of the Match.
Shadab Khan praised the pitch and called it bit slower compared to Perth and has a spin as well.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was delayed due to rain.
The game was shortened to 14 overs after rain.
D/L method was used due to rain intervention.
